7"><a href="https://civileats.com/category/environment/food-waste/">Food Waste</a></li><li class="cat-item cat-item-205"><a href="https://civileats.com/category/environment/gmos/">GMOs</a></li><li class="cat-item cat-item-3265"><a href="https://civileats.com/category/environment/pesticides/">Pesticides</a></li><li class="cat-item cat-item-4369"><a href="https://civileats.com/category/environment/seafood/">Seafood</a></li><li class="cat-item cat-item-11114"><a href="https://civileats.com/category/environment/water/">Water</a></li></ul></div></div></li><li role="menuitem"> <a class="orange" href="https://civileats.com/donate/">DONATE</a></li></ul></div><div id="header-search" class="search-overlay"> <a href="javascript:void(0)" class="closebtn" onclick="closeNav()">&times;</a><div class="search-overlay-content"><form method="get" action="https://civileats.com"> <input type="search" value="Search" name="s" class="searchbox" onFocus="if (this.value == 'Search') {this.value = '';}" onBlur="if (this.value == '') {this.value = 'Search';}"> <input type="image" src="" class="icon-search search-submit" alt=" "></form></div></div><div class="search-button"> <span onclick="openNav()"><div class="icon-search"></div></span></div><ul class="social"><li><a class="icon-instagram" href="https://www.instagram.com/civileats/" target="_blank"></a></li><li><a class="icon-twitter" href="http://www.twitter.com/CivilEats" target="_blank"></a></li><li><a class="icon-facebook icon-fb-spacing" href="https://www.facebook.com/CivilEats/" target="_blank"></a></li><li><a class="icon-rss icon-rss-spacing" href="http://feeds.feedburner.com/civileats/" target="_blank"></a></li></ul></div></div><div id="header-break"></div><div id="posttop"><h1>A Decade of Pesticides, GMOs, and Alternatives to Chemical-Intensive Farming</h1><h2><p>Four experts discuss how the last 10 years have seen an increase in pesticides—and crops bred to resist them—even as consumer concerns have mounted.</p></h2></div><div id="postimg"> <img src="https://civileats.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/190410-civil-eats-roundtable-gmos-pesticides-trends-top-1-1200x800.jpg" alt=""></div><div id="article"><div id="postmeta"> <span class="postmeta-author">By <a href="https://civileats.com/author/civil-eats/" title="Posts by The Civil Eats Editors" class="author url fn" rel="author">The Civil Eats Editors</a></span><br> <span class="postmeta-cat"><a href="https://civileats.com/category/10th-anniversary/" rel="category tag">10th Anniversary</a>, <a href="https://civileats.com/category/farming/" rel="category tag">FARMING</a>, <a href="https://civileats.com/category/health/" rel="category tag">HEALTH</a>, <a href="https://civileats.com/category/environment/pesticides/" rel="category tag">Pesticides</a></span><br> <span class="postmeta-date">Posted on: April 10, 2019</span> <span class="postmeta-sep">&nbsp;|&nbsp;</span> <span class="postmeta-comments"><a href="https://civileats.com/2019/04/10/a-decade-of-pesticides-gmos-and-alternatives-to-chemical-intensive-farming/#respond">5 Comments</a></span><div class="side-social"> <a 
